\begin_layout Standard
A music is a set of notes executed at a given time.
 Each note has a duration and an amplitude (loudness).
 The notes are divided in 
\series bold
octaves
\series default
, each octave consists of the notes between two consecutive Do inclusive.
 However many instruments provides more than 8 notes for each octave and
 those particular notes are called semitones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It should be taken into account that each note has its own well defined
 frequency, take for instance the 3
\begin_inset script superscript

\begin_layout Plain Layout
rd
\end_layout

\end_inset

